Introduction 

This project was completed as part of the Digital Literacy course to understand the importance of digital tools and online responsibility. As a Student Digital Ambassador, the goal was to create awareness about digital literacy among peers. The project includes creating an infographic, building a professional online presence, exploring coding and collaboration platforms, learning email etiquette, and understanding cybercrime. Through these tasks, I gained practical knowledge about using digital platforms effectively, communicating professionally, and staying safe online. This project helped me develop essential skills that will be useful throughout my academic journey and future career.

Task 1: Digital Literacy Infographic

For this task, I created a digital literacy infographic using Canva. The infographic explains the meaning of digital literacy, highlights important digital tools for students, and provides tips for safe internet practices. I focused on making the design simple, visually appealing, and easy to understand. The infographic includes points such as using strong passwords, avoiding suspicious links, and maintaining a professional online presence.

While working on this task, I found Canva easy to use, but selecting the right design and arranging content properly was slightly challenging. It was interesting to explore different templates and customize them according to my needs. This task helped me understand how visual content can effectively spread awareness and communicate information quickly.

Task 2: Digital Portfolio 

In this task, I created my professional digital portfolio by setting up profiles on platforms like GitHub and LinkedIn. GitHub is used to showcase coding projects and track progress, while LinkedIn helps in building a professional network and connecting with industry professionals.

I updated my GitHub profile by creating a README file that includes my name, branch, and learning goals. On LinkedIn, I added my education details, including my degree and university. These platforms will help me in the future to showcase my skills, apply for internships, and build my professional identity.

Over the next four years, I plan to regularly update my profiles, upload projects, and connect with professionals. This task helped me understand the importance of having a strong digital presence.

Task 3: Platforms

In this task, I explored coding and collaboration platforms. I created an account on HackerRank and solved a beginner-level problem, which helped me understand basic programming concepts and improve my problem-solving skills.

Additionally, I created a Google Form titled “Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz” with five questions. The form includes both multiple-choice and short-answer questions. It can be used to test students’ knowledge about digital literacy.

This task was very useful as it introduced me to platforms that are important for both learning and collaboration. Coding platforms help in improving programming skills, while tools like Google Forms are useful for collecting data and conducting quizzes. These skills will help me academically and in future projects.

Task 4: Email Etiquette 

In this task, I learned how to write professional emails and follow proper communication etiquette. I wrote two emails: one requesting an assignment extension from a professor and another applying for an internship. Both emails included a clear subject line, polite tone, and proper structure.

I also created a checklist of social media do’s and don’ts to promote responsible online behavior. I learned that poor communication can lead to misunderstandings. For example, sending an email without a proper subject or greeting may appear rude and may not get a response.

This task helped me understand the importance of clear, respectful, and professional communication in digital platforms.

Task 5: Cybercrime Awareness

In this task, I studied cybercrime, specifically UPI fraud. I learned how fraudsters trick people into sharing sensitive information like OTPs and passwords. I also created a prevention checklist to help users stay safe online.

I was surprised to see how common such frauds are and how easily people can become victims. Even a small mistake can lead to financial loss. This task made me more aware of digital security.

One habit I will change is being more cautious while clicking on links and sharing personal information online. I will also spread awareness among others about staying safe from cybercrime.

Conclusion 

This project provided me with a comprehensive understanding of digital literacy and its importance in today’s world. I learned how to use digital tools effectively, build a professional online presence, communicate properly, and stay safe from cyber threats. Each task contributed to developing practical skills that are essential for students. This project not only improved my technical knowledge but also increased my awareness of responsible digital behavior. Overall, it was a valuable learning experience that will help me in both academic and professional life.

